-- Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, Chimei, Formosa Petrochemical
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-16T05:47:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/taiwan-stocks-au-optronics-chimei-formosa-petrochemical-umc.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index fell 0.8 percent to 8,054.94 and
gained 0.5 percent this week.  China-related companies:  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT), a
flat-panel maker, advanced 2 percent to NT$15.50, the biggest
advance since March 9.  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT) increased
1.7 percent to NT$15.30.   Taiwan ’s cabinet yesterday approved a
relaxation of caps on Chinese investment in five industries,
including flat panels and semiconductors, the Economic Daily
News reported, without citing anyone.  Emile Chang, deputy executive secretary of Taiwan’s
investment commission, and Fan Liang-Tung, the commission’s
executive secretary, couldn’t be immediately reached for comment
as they are in a meeting.  Formosa Petrochemical Corp. (6505)  (6505 TT) dropped 2.2 percent
to NT$93.40, the biggest loss since Feb. 1. Net income in 2011
fell to NT$22.5 billion from NT$40.90 billion a year earlier,
according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
